    <title>New item proposal</title>
    <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Trade&amp;message.id=13801</link>
    <description>&lt;DIV&gt;While I am farming items to make SeruBane, ShissarBane, VampyreBane, ZekBane, UndeadBane and HumanoidBane, I thought would it be nice that the final combine would result in an Augmentation with Bane DMG instead of a Bane weapon?&amp;nbsp; I know a lot of banked gear would get a new lease on life as a Bane weapon.&amp;nbsp; And there are a few things you can put in to the Augmentation to prevent it&amp;nbsp;from becoming too powerful.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;It would look something like this...&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;A Small Condensed Mist Emerald&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;MAGIC ITEM LORE ITEM NO TRADE AUGMENTATION&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;This Augmentation fits in slot types: 4, 8&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Bane DMG: Shissar 7&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Restrictions -&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;1h Weapons Only&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Min delay: 20&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Slot: PRIMARY SECONDARY HANDS&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Required level of 50.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Class:&amp;nbsp; WAR PAL RNG SHD BRD MNK BST ROG&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The minimum delay is added to prevent game breaking combination like adding this aug to some extremely low delay weapon like the Mosscovered Twig.&amp;nbsp; The HANDS slot is there to be compatible with a few weapons out there that's also usable armor; it will not create any exploits because the Bane DMG is not in affect when worn as a armor.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Bane augs like these can be added to complement existing Bane weapons for legacy events, or be added for future events.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
